Uh… the military voters followed the ballot directions as best they could. I don’t know if you fully understand their situation. They were deployed overseas; they did not have the opportunity to stop by the balloting areas in Florida to drop off their ballots. In fact they couldn’t even go to a post office to mail it out. Their votes were not counted because of a hyper-technicality. There was no way possible for them to get their ballots to the ballot counters in time. They weren’t overseas by their personal choice; duty to their country required them to be there. The same country that decided their votes didn’t count because Al Gore’s lawyers wanted Al Gore to win at any cost. That was absolute bullshit.<br>
