That's the beauty of this whole thing - it shows the flaws in many systems.  The military obviously neglects to follow standard postal procedures like the rest of us and it cost that poor fellow his vote.  The post mark is a legal binding stamp - where as his letter was probably dropped off by a military clerk with a bunch of other letters.  <br>
<br>
The military is using their own courrier service and it's obviously flawed if there is no legal receipt proving when it was delivered.  USPS, FedEx, DHL, and any other service has signatures for each package that are legal too.<br>
<br>
Not only do they need to improve the ballot system, but they need to get the military to validate their own mail for their employees or use another delivery service.  <br>
<br>
VERY SAD.<br>
